FBIS3-50747 "drlat005_m_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 Brazil Army Minister Rules Out `Any Possibility' of Coup PY0701113194 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in Portuguese 0900 GMT 7 Jan 94 PY0701113194 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] Army Minister Zenildo Zoroastro has ruled out any possibility of a coup in Brazil. There is no risk of Fujimorization in Brazil, the minister said, noting that President Itamar Franco has already said everything that had to be said on the subject. The military ministers had thought about releasing a note denying the statements by Justice Minister Mauricio Correa. The ministers, however, preferred not to promote greater controversy on the subject.
